														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-423628">
									

<p>I had not seen SCP-410 before I wrote and posted this. I do have to admit I've not managed to make it through all the SCP's yet.</p>
<p>The ability is similar, but not exactly identical.</p>
<p>SCP-758's ability is limited to correcting breaches in technical rules only and does not enable it to change the content of the text as is shown in paragraph three of SCP-410's description.</p>
<p>Also, SCP-410 is not capable of applying it's ability to digital mediums or spoken language as SCP-758 is.</p>
<p>If senior staff feel these differences are not significant enough to warrant keeping SCP-758 around, I am up for any suggestions as to how I might make it worth holding on to. If we can't find a way to make it work, I have no problem with it being decommissioned or deleted. This is, after all, only my first attempt.</p>

							</div>

								
